expression = re.compile(rfc._DOMAIN_AV_REGEX)
bad_examples = ['domain=a', 'Domain= a-7', 'Dom=foo-77.a-7.aa',
    'Domain=127.1.1', 'Domain=127.a.1.1',
    'Domain=2001:0dg8:0000:0000:0000:ff00:0042:8329', 'Domain=7',
    'Domain=-', 'Domain=a.-aa', 'Domain=a.7aa', 'Domain=a-', 'Domain=a.',
    'Domain=.a', 'Domain=']
for bad_example in bad_examples:
    self.assertFalse(bool(expression.fullmatch(bad_example)), msg=
        "Bad Domain AV '{m}' matched by regex".format(m=bad_example))
